Sentencas: A cermet-supported tubular configuration amenable to preparation by a relatively low-cost thermal spraying process is proposed.
Titulo: Development of a Ni/Al2O3 Cermet-Supported Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Assembled with Different Functional Layers by Atmospheric Plasma-Spraying

Sentencas: An Al2O3-Ni cermet thick deposit prepared by flame spraying is employed as both support tube and anode current collector.
Titulo: Development of a Ni/Al2O3 Cermet-Supported Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Assembled with Different Functional Layers by Atmospheric Plasma-Spraying

Sentencas: Atmospheric plasma spraying (APS) has been employed to prepare the anode, cathode, and stabilized ZrO2-based electrolyte with the aim of reducing manufacturing costs.
Titulo: Development of a Ni/Al2O3 Cermet-Supported Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Assembled with Different Functional Layers by Atmospheric Plasma-Spraying

Sentencas: Gas-tightness of the APS electrolyte has been achieved by a postdensification process.
Titulo: Development of a Ni/Al2O3 Cermet-Supported Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Assembled with Different Functional Layers by Atmospheric Plasma-Spraying

Sentencas: The effects of the densification process on the gas-tightness of the plasma-sprayed YSZ electrolyte and the open-circuit voltage of the SOFC have been investigated.
Titulo: Development of a Ni/Al2O3 Cermet-Supported Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Assembled with Different Functional Layers by Atmospheric Plasma-Spraying

Sentencas: The effects of the microstructures of the plasma-sprayed anode, electrolyte, and cathode on the performance of the SOFC test cell have been investigated.
Titulo: Development of a Ni/Al2O3 Cermet-Supported Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Assembled with Different Functional Layers by Atmospheric Plasma-Spraying
